<TEI.2 ID="ch027"><TEIHEADER><FILEDESC><TITLESTMT><TITLE>Letter, 1838 June 12, Washington to C.A. Harris / Jno. [i.e., John] Ross: a machine-readable transcription</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cherokee Nation. Principal Chief (1828-1866 : Ross)</AUTHOR><RESPSTMT><RESP>Creation of machine-readable version:</RESP><NAME>Lesli Wall Zimmerman</NAME><NAME>Debra Jean Roney</NAME></RESPSTMT></TITLESTMT><PUBLICATIONSTMT><PUBLISHER>The University of Tennessee Libraries</PUBLISHER><PUBPLACE>Knoxville, TN</PUBPLACE><ADDRESS><ADDRLINE>Hoskins Library - Special Collections</ADDRLINE><ADDRLINE>The University of Tennessee</ADDRLINE><ADDRLINE>Knoxville, TN 37996</ADDRLINE></ADDRESS><DATE>2000</DATE><IDNO>ch027</IDNO><IDNO>OCLC: 44803407</IDNO><AVAILABILITY STATUS="FREE"><P>This work is the property of The Tennessee State Library and Archives, Nashville, TN.  It may be used freely by individuals for research, teaching, and personal use as long as this statement of availability is included in the text.</P></AVAILABILITY></PUBLICATIONSTMT><SOURCEDESC><BIBL><TITLE>Letter, 1838 June 12, Washington to C.A. Harris / Jno. [i.e., John] Ross</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cherokee Nation. Principal Chief (1828-1866 : Ross)</AUTHOR><DATE VALUE="1838-06-12">June 12, 1838</DATE><EXTENT>2p</EXTENT><NOTE TYPE="summary">This is a copy of a letter from John Ross to C.A. Harris, commissioner of Indian Affairs, dated June 12, 1838.  Ross applies to Harris for payment for Hair Conrad, Jesse Bushyhead, Thomas Woodward, and Major Pole Cat, who acted as mediators to the Seminoles in Florida.</NOTE><NOTE TYPE="repository">The Tennessee State Library and Archives, Nashville, TN</NOTE><NOTE TYPE="collection">State Library Cherokee Collection</NOTE><NOTE TYPE="box"> 1</NOTE><NOTE TYPE="folder"> 23</NOTE><NOTE TYPE="document">ch027</NOTE></BIBL></SOURCEDESC></FILEDESC><ENCODINGDESC><PROJECTDESC><P>Prepared for The University of Tennessee Digital Library</P></PROJECTDESC><EDITORIALDECL><P>Quotation marks retained as data except inside q tags</P><P>Errors in transcription of the printed text controlled with Microsoft Word spell-checker; text has also been thoroughly proofread.</P><P>Corrections and normalization represented by editorial tags.</P><P>All unambiguous end-of-line hyphens removed. </P><P>Catchwords and directional notes such as "turn page over" have been omitted.</P></EDITORIALDECL><REFSDECL><P>ID attributes provided for only those pages, chapters, or illustrations toward which a reference or figure points</P></REFSDECL><CLASSDECL><TAXONOMY ID="LCSH"><BIBL><TITLE>Library of Congress Subject Headings</TITLE></BIBL></TAXONOMY></CLASSDECL></ENCODINGDESC><PROFILEDESC><TEXTCLASS><KEYWORDS SCHEME="LCSH"><LIST><ITEM>Letters</ITEM><ITEM>Indian agents</ITEM><ITEM>Seminole Indians</ITEM><ITEM>Florida</ITEM></LIST> </KEYWORDS></TEXTCLASS></PROFILEDESC></TEIHEADER><TEXT><BODY><DIV1 TYPE="letter"><PB N="[1]"><OPENER><DATELINE><ADDRESS><ADDRLINE><NAME TYPE="place">Washington City</NAME></ADDRLINE></ADDRESS><DATE VALUE="1838-06-12">June 12th 1838</DATE></DATELINE> <SALUTE><NAME TYPE="person">C.A Harris</NAME> Esq. <ABBR EXPAN="Commissioner" TYPE="contraction">Commr.</ABBR> of Indian Affairs<LB>Sir/</SALUTE></OPENER><P>I herewith submit for payment the accounts of <NAME TYPE="person">Hair Conrad</NAME>, <NAME TYPE="person">Jesse Bushyhead</NAME>, <NAME TYPE="person"><ABBR EXPAN="Thomas">Thos.</ABBR> Woodward</NAME> and <NAME TYPE="person">Major Pole Cat</NAME> for services and expenses <DEL TYPE="overstrike">incurred</DEL> as Mediators of peace to the <NAME TYPE="person">Seminoles</NAME> of <NAME TYPE="place">Florida</NAME>-  Also, their powers of Attorney appointing me as their Agent in the premises.</P><P>It is proper <ADD PLACE="supralinear">for me</ADD> distinctly for me to explain, that although I have here acquiesced in the deductions required by the Department, I, as Agent and Acting in behalf of the above named persons, do not mean thereby to prejudice the right of claiming from the <NAME TYPE="place">United States</NAME> the sums they deducted from the Original accounts in the Memorial of the Deputation to Congress bearing date <DATE VALUE="1838-03-21">March 21st. 1838</DATE>&mdash;.</P><CLOSER><SALUTE>I am Sir, <ABBR EXPAN="Your Obedient Servant" TYPE="contraction">Yr. Obt. Sert.</ABBR></SALUTE><LB>
<SIGNED><NAME TYPE="person"><ABBR EXPAN="John">Jno</ABBR> Ross</NAME></SIGNED></CLOSER></DIV1></BODY><BACK><DIV1 TYPE="letter"><PB N="[2]"><P>Copy of a letter to <NAME TYPE="person">C.A. Harris</NAME> <ABBR EXPAN="Esquire">Esqr.</ABBR> Commissioner of Indian Affairs- respecting the claims of the <NAME TYPE="person">Cherokee</NAME> Mediators&mdash;<DATE VALUE="1838-06-12">June 12th. 1838</DATE></P></DIV1></BACK></TEXT></TEI.2>
